          <source>You can use a webhook to trigger an Azure function, and then parse the payload to determine what happened and how to respond.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Suppose you are a developer in an IT department.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
